[h1]The font-variant Property [/h1]

The CSS font-variant property allows you to convert your font to all small caps. The values can be set as [b]normal[/b], [b]small-caps[/b], and [b]inherit[/b]. 

[b]The HTML:[/b] [code format="html" ]<p class="normal">Paragraph font variant set to normal.</p>
<p class="small">Paragraph font variant set to small-caps.</p>[/code]
[b]The CSS:[/b] [code format="css" codeId="518"]p.normal {
   font-variant: [b]normal[/b];
}
p.small {
   font-variant: [b]small-caps[/b];
}[/code]
[b]Result:[/b] [img id="2594" width="100%"]
[note]Not every font supports CSS font-variant, so be sure to test before you publish.[/note]
